# .env  —  settings Docker Compose reads automatically.
#
# AIRFLOW_UID makes files created by the containers owned by YOU (avoids
# permission problems). On Mac / Linux / WSL, the best value is your user id.
#
# The easy way to create the real .env is to run this in the project folder:
#     echo "AIRFLOW_UID=$(id -u)" > .env
#
# If you can't run that, 50000 is a safe default:

AIRFLOW_UID=50000
